Sis.

25
00:02:04,020 --> 00:02:04,860
Sis!

26
00:02:07,580 --> 00:02:08,540
What did you call me?

27
00:02:11,020 --> 00:02:12,340
I called you... Liu Yan.

28
00:02:12,700 --> 00:02:14,110
That's not respectful.

29
00:02:14,650 --> 00:02:15,870
Don't call me by my name again.

30
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,130
Liu Yan, you can't

31
00:02:18,130 --> 00:02:19,020
hide things from me...

32
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:20,620
I just said that.

33
00:02:21,320 --> 00:02:22,260
What should you call me?

34
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:23,940
Sis.

35
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,720
Mr. Lu, talk to her.

36
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:31,080
You really scared us both.

37
00:02:31,420 --> 00:02:32,880
He thought you wouldn't make it back.

38
00:02:36,210 --> 00:02:37,500
Today's not my treat, by the way.

39
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:38,760
Don't try to overcharge.

40
00:02:40,260 --> 00:02:41,540
Alright, Sis.

41
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:43,380
Let's go.

42
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:44,940
Come on, let's go.

43
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:46,980
Is the ground burning?

44
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:47,940
A little bit.

45
00:02:55,380 --> 00:02:56,630
I was afraid you'd make a fuss,

46
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:58,380
so I asked you to stay at home.
Why did you tell him?

47
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,250
Mr. Lu was really great today.

48
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:01,730
He didn't even mention money all day.

49
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:03,420
And he had a client to meet today,

50
00:03:03,420 --> 00:03:04,280
but he skipped it.

51
00:03:04,860 --> 00:03:06,290
Kids can't tell who's family, huh?

52
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:07,680
Mr. Lu was concerned

53
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:08,640
about Mr. Luo.

54
00:03:09,620 --> 00:03:11,470
Don't say I'm out to hurt anyone.

55
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:12,950
That never crossed my mind.

56
00:03:17,930 --> 00:03:19,540
I said it, so what?

57
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:21,640
What do you think of me?

58
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:23,650
Hey, you tied me up

59
00:03:23,650 --> 00:03:24,530
like I'm your prey.

60
00:03:24,530 --> 00:03:25,480
What else would I think?

61
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:26,580
Go get a manicure?

62
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,010
Didn't delay your work, did it?

63
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:31,620
No.

64
00:03:32,090 --> 00:03:33,500
You came out with all limbs intact,

65
00:03:33,660 --> 00:03:34,780
which calls for a big celebration.

66
00:03:35,490 --> 00:03:36,840
Didn't they give you trouble?

67
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:39,140
No.

68
00:03:42,060 --> 00:03:43,680
I do use my brain, you know.

69
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,500
I had a complete

70
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:45,900
offense and defense strategy planned

71
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,810
before daring to approach Mr. Luo.

72
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,180
Alright, alright.

73
00:03:49,540 --> 00:03:50,520
I suggest you

74
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:52,300
abandon these dangerous ideas.

75
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,340
Don't even think about it again.

76
00:03:53,340 --> 00:03:54,460
Remember that, okay?

77
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:58,620
That's a lot of money, so much!

78
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:00,400
- Don't touch it.
- You killed someone

79
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,450
- Put it down.
- or set a fire?

80
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,250
What did they force you to do?

81
00:04:04,140 --> 00:04:04,980
Take him to school.

82
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:06,100
Take me to school?

83
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,030
Taking me to school right now?

84
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,780
Did you do something illegal?

85
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:11,290
Did you skip class again today?

86
00:04:11,870 --> 00:04:14,410
Li Zan, can you please stop skipping?

87
00:04:14,410 --> 00:04:15,310
Is this the right time

88
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:16,150
to discuss this?

89
00:04:16,150 --> 00:04:17,940
How am I supposed to go to school
with all this money?

90
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,260
Can't you see she is crazy?

91
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:21,710
What are you doing?

92
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:23,420
Should we go to the Civil Affairs Bureau

93
00:04:23,420 --> 00:04:24,280
to prove she's insane?

94
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:25,130
Then she wouldn't have

95
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:26,190
to be your guardian, okay?

96
00:04:26,590 --> 00:04:28,300
Right, I can't be your guardian.

97
00:04:28,820 --> 00:04:29,930
I'll take you to see Ms. He.

98
00:04:29,950 --> 00:04:30,770
Let her take care of you.

99
00:04:53,170 --> 00:04:54,010
I...

100
00:04:57,790 --> 00:04:58,640
I want to make a will.

101
00:05:00,990 --> 00:05:02,130
Mr. Luo and I signed

102
00:05:02,130 --> 00:05:03,380
a new fight agreement.

103
00:05:04,140 --> 00:05:04,980
A real fight.

104
00:05:06,340 --> 00:05:08,010
I've never heard

105
00:05:08,010 --> 00:05:09,590
of making a will before boxing.

106
00:05:10,740 --> 00:05:11,810
So what's with

107
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:14,260
this bag of money?

108
00:05:14,780 --> 00:05:15,620
Tell me the truth.

109
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,090
Otherwise, I won't take it.

110
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:21,660
I'm going to fight the Big Beast.

111
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,390
If I win,

112
00:05:23,650 --> 00:05:24,860
the debt will get cleared.

113
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:26,590
Plus, I'll get an appearance fee.

114
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:28,740
But if I lose...

115
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:33,020
I can't lose.

116
00:05:34,090 --> 00:05:35,470
This is the advance appearance fee.

117
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:38,180
Big Beast is...

118
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:42,750
Yeah, that Big Beast.

119
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:49,960
That guy's arms are
as thick as my thighs.

120
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:51,440
You can't fight him.
He's like three of you.

121
00:05:51,440 --> 00:05:52,280
You know that?

122
00:05:55,260 --> 00:05:56,620
So the draw of this match

123
00:05:56,620 --> 00:05:57,740
is spectators watching you

124
00:05:57,740 --> 00:05:58,880
get beaten to death live?

125
00:05:59,060 --> 00:05:59,980
If I lose,

126
00:06:00,410 --> 00:06:02,340
all the money goes to Li Zan.

127
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,490
That won't even cover your debt!

128
00:06:04,620 --> 00:06:05,460
If you lose,

129
00:06:05,460 --> 00:06:06,580
what happens to Li Zan if you die?

130
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:11,060
You shouldn't fight.

131
00:06:13,910 --> 00:06:16,040
Mr. Luo doesn't allow backing out.

132
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,220
It's not without room for negotiation.

133
00:06:18,220 --> 00:06:20,060
I have some money left.

134
00:06:20,060 --> 00:06:21,400
I could loan you some.

135
00:06:21,790 --> 00:06:23,540
Being alive is good enough.

136
00:06:23,540 --> 00:06:24,750
Why risk your life for nothing?

137
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:28,200
I've thought about it.

138
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:30,050
I even thought of going back to Beijing.

139
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,590
Jiang Fang's been gone for years.

140
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:35,030
I can consider her dead.

141
00:06:36,340 --> 00:06:38,310
Li Zan and I aren't even related.

142
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:39,580
I could pretend he doesn't exist.

143
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:42,920
But even if I go back to Beijing,

144
00:06:43,180 --> 00:06:44,340
what's there?

145
00:06:44,900 --> 00:06:45,820
Just a childhood friend

146
00:06:46,350 --> 00:06:48,310
who always gets scolded because of me.

147
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:51,020
I used to live as a sparring partner,

148
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:52,260
waiting for my mom.

149
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:54,420
Now I live to repay debts.

150
00:06:56,220 --> 00:06:57,060
Nothing more.

151
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:00,620
Your arguments are...

152
00:07:02,620 --> 00:07:03,830
Maybe I should go find Tattooed Arms.

153
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:04,850
There must be another way.

154
00:07:04,850 --> 00:07:06,120
Don't worry about it.

155
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,500
I've already made up my mind.

156
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,020
Can't you ever listen to advice?

157
00:07:11,060 --> 00:07:12,340
I get what you're saying,

158
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,820
but sometimes I don't want to hear it.

159
00:07:16,380 --> 00:07:17,340
I can't explain why.

160
00:07:19,670 --> 00:07:20,920
Do you think everything

161
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:22,350
you do for Jiang Fang is worth it?

162
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:30,380
I want to add another clause.

163
00:07:31,090 --> 00:07:32,700
If I die at the match,

164
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:33,990
cancel my family's debts.

165
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,090
Don't make my brother or my mom repay.

166
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:39,100
Is your life

167
00:07:39,980 --> 00:07:40,860
that valuable?

168
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:43,140
Not really, Mr. Luo.

169
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,430
But it'll make the match intense

170
00:07:45,690 --> 00:07:46,660
and marketable.

171
00:07:47,340 --> 00:07:48,820
You know that better than I do.

172
00:07:49,140 --> 00:07:51,540
That kid isn't your real brother, is he?

173
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:55,580
He's not, actually.

174
00:07:56,170 --> 00:07:57,430
But the debts belong to me and my mom.

175
00:07:58,100 --> 00:07:59,140
He's not involved in this.

176
00:08:00,310 --> 00:08:01,180
Yet he genuinely

177
00:08:01,180 --> 00:08:02,210
suffers because of my mom.

178
00:08:02,740 --> 00:08:03,740
I'm obligated

179
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:05,340
to make up for her mistakes.

180
00:08:06,010 --> 00:08:07,460
I'm her daughter after all, right?

181
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,510
Is it really worth all this for her?

182
00:08:15,810 --> 00:08:17,340
If I really lose it all,

183
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:18,750
Li Zan will finally be free.

184
00:08:19,570 --> 00:08:20,500
Jiang Fang will be free too.

185
00:08:20,780 --> 00:08:21,620
I don't lose out.

186
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:32,350
So you've made up your mind?

187
00:08:32,380 --> 00:08:33,220
Yeah, I'm sure.

188
00:08:35,930 --> 00:08:37,180
First, let's open a bank account

189
00:08:38,220 --> 00:08:39,510
and deposit this money.

190
00:08:39,970 --> 00:08:41,060
Sign some authorizations.

191
00:08:41,620 --> 00:08:42,820
I'll handle the will

192
00:08:44,230 --> 00:08:45,080
for you.

193
00:08:49,420 --> 00:08:51,140
Lu Tianchi, you're such a worrier!

194
00:08:51,340 --> 00:08:52,380
Look at you, all nervous.

195
00:08:53,570 --> 00:08:54,850
Alright, stop joking.

196
00:08:55,740 --> 00:08:56,720
Hurry up and get it done.

197
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:58,050
I'll handle other matters for you.

198
00:08:59,060 --> 00:08:59,940
Why'd you run off?

199
00:09:26,820 --> 00:09:29,340
(Lin's Herbal Tea, Grocery)

200
00:09:29,340 --> 00:09:32,220
(Call me and you'll win.
There must be money.)

201
00:09:39,820 --> 00:09:42,420
(Will)

202
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:46,460
What brings you here?

203
00:09:51,020 --> 00:09:52,080
Uncle Lu,

204
00:09:53,460 --> 00:09:56,020
my sis took so much money.

205
00:09:57,700 --> 00:09:59,900
Is she becoming someone's mistress?

206
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:07,890
As a young person,

207
00:10:07,890 --> 00:10:08,780
isn't this mindset

208
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:09,780
rather abnormal?

209
00:10:10,220 --> 00:10:11,650
Do young women have to

210
00:10:11,650 --> 00:10:13,580
give in to some older guy

211
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:14,720
just to get ahead?

212
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:16,100
Or is she selling a kidney now?

213
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:17,750
Are you insane?

214
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:18,830
She's selling her kidney?

215
00:10:18,830 --> 00:10:19,960
You think she runs a butcher shop?

216
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:21,460
Listen,

217
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:22,760
don't try to get info out of me.

218
00:10:23,310 --> 00:10:24,540
Your sis is my client.

219
00:10:25,010 --> 00:10:26,020
I must respect

220
00:10:26,020 --> 00:10:26,940
her privacy.

221
00:10:27,310 --> 00:10:28,860
Right, Uncle Lu.

222
00:10:29,820 --> 00:10:31,310
But my sis, you know,

223
00:10:31,310 --> 00:10:32,240
is pretty hot-tempered.

224
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:33,740
If I ask her,

225
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:35,300
she'll likely beat me up.

226
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:36,900
You've tasted her fists before,

227
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:38,100
right?

228
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:41,060
Don't act chummy with me.

229
00:10:41,060 --> 00:10:42,370
Calling me "Uncle Lu" won't help.

230
00:10:42,370 --> 00:10:43,190
Who's your uncle?

231
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:44,180
Uncle Lu,

232
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:46,980
I'm like half-family to her.

233
00:10:47,140 --> 00:10:48,940
Only we two can truly

234
00:10:49,220 --> 00:10:50,660
rely on

235
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:52,400
and look out for each other.

236
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:53,900
Don't you agree?

237
00:11:00,490 --> 00:11:01,480
Do you really mean that?

238
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,060
I swear, I really do.

239
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:05,820
She has her own plans.

240
00:11:06,420 --> 00:11:08,420
My advice is,

241
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:09,820
don't get in her way.

242
00:11:10,020 --> 00:11:11,750
She has plans? What plans?

243
00:11:11,890 --> 00:11:13,350
Come on, give more details.

244
00:11:15,610 --> 00:11:16,620
You're cunning, huh?

245
00:11:16,980 --> 00:11:18,700
Hey, it's just a chat.

246
00:11:20,660 --> 00:11:21,500
Your free time

247
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:22,340
is almost up.

248
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:23,660
Want me to give you

249
00:11:23,660 --> 00:11:25,080
a special discount slot?

250
00:11:26,540 --> 00:11:27,380
You go do your thing.

251
00:11:27,380 --> 00:11:28,630
I'm heading home to do homework.

252
00:11:31,260 --> 00:11:32,490
Fix that broken door, okay?

253
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:12,200
I've realized

254
00:12:12,570 --> 00:12:14,130
it's dangerous to live with you

255
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:15,030
or Jiang Fang.

256
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:16,750
It's too easy to get brainwashed

257
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:17,880
by your cooking.

258
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:27,610
Eat later.

259
00:12:27,610 --> 00:12:29,300
Have some when it's ready.

260
00:12:29,420 --> 00:12:30,660
I'll just have one bite.

261
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:32,200
It won't make a difference.

262
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:38,180
- Tastes amazing.
- It'll get even better!

263
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:56,810
Look.

264
00:12:56,940 --> 00:12:58,500
Look at these layers.

265
00:12:59,260 --> 00:13:00,540
So good. I...

266
00:13:00,540 --> 00:13:01,500
Let's toast.

267
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:02,340
Alright.

268
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:04,100
Hold on!

269
00:13:05,140 --> 00:13:06,940
May I gain weight successfully.

270
00:13:16,460 --> 00:13:17,420
This is just delicious.

271
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:19,940
Best thing I've ever tasted.

272
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:21,740
Well,

273
00:13:23,230 --> 00:13:24,260
that thing with Mr. Luo...

274
00:13:24,940 --> 00:13:25,820
I advise caution.

275
00:13:29,020 --> 00:13:30,020
What do you even know?

276
00:13:30,990 --> 00:13:32,020
Mr. Lu told me everything.

277
00:13:32,540 --> 00:13:33,380
No way that's true.

278
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,290
He never spills secrets.

279
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:39,500
Everything has a price.

280
00:13:41,130 --> 00:13:42,820
He has to handle this stuff.

281
00:13:46,230 --> 00:13:48,000
My sis took so much money.

282
00:13:48,180 --> 00:13:50,060
I'm giving you this info

283
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:51,020
about her plan.

284
00:13:51,020 --> 00:13:52,180
Alright, that's how it is.

285
00:13:52,180 --> 00:13:53,120
Just get the gist, okay?

286
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:53,930
I've got my own plan too.

287
00:13:53,930 --> 00:13:54,760
