866
00:41:29,980 --> 00:41:31,330
He's a total liar!

867
00:41:31,330 --> 00:41:33,380
But my sister is my real sister!

868
00:41:33,830 --> 00:41:34,740
I'm jumping!

869
00:41:34,740 --> 00:41:35,690
Go on, jump.

870
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:36,880
I'll count to three.

871
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:38,040
Hey man,

872
00:41:38,040 --> 00:41:39,590
come on, just let me go down.

873
00:41:39,590 --> 00:41:40,430
Three!

874
00:41:40,980 --> 00:41:43,160
♪Cold wind blows♪

875
00:41:44,260 --> 00:41:46,490
♪Snow fills the sky♪

876
00:41:46,860 --> 00:41:55,350
♪Where is my way ahead♪

877
00:42:01,650 --> 00:42:02,570
Hey man,

878
00:42:02,570 --> 00:42:03,780
what line of work are you in?

879
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:05,730
What exactly is this for?

880
00:42:06,370 --> 00:42:07,590
We owed a mountain of debt.

881
00:42:08,410 --> 00:42:10,050
She's about to pay it back
with her life.

882
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:11,880
She told me to come up here and leave.

883
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:12,780
I...

884
00:42:13,560 --> 00:42:14,500
Could I really leave?

885
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:16,980
My parents never cared about me.

886
00:42:16,980 --> 00:42:18,460
Finally, I had a sister.

887
00:42:18,460 --> 00:42:19,930
She was willing to care about me.

888
00:42:19,930 --> 00:42:21,990
Someone cooked meals for me.

889
00:42:22,110 --> 00:42:23,890
Someone urged me to go to school.

890
00:42:23,890 --> 00:42:25,740
When someone genuinely worried about me,

891
00:42:26,050 --> 00:42:28,370
I'm about to lose my sister!

892
00:42:28,370 --> 00:42:30,450
Please, let me get off.

893
00:42:55,320 --> 00:43:00,080
♪Mother, I've grown up♪

894
00:43:02,180 --> 00:43:09,120
♪No longer crave my embrace♪

895
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:16,320
♪No longer need my approval♪

896
00:43:17,010 --> 00:43:23,460
♪No longer afraid
to realize I'm still here♪

897
00:43:24,420 --> 00:43:27,870
♪Countless disappointments;
nothing left to hope for♪

898
00:43:28,110 --> 00:43:31,770
♪We're falling through the air,
endlessly falling down♪

899
00:43:31,770 --> 00:43:35,290
♪There's nothing we can hold on to♪

900
00:43:35,710 --> 00:43:40,010
♪No ground where we can land safely♪

901
00:43:41,460 --> 00:43:43,350
♪(When all hope is gone)♪

902
00:43:43,350 --> 00:43:49,260
♪Our hearts will break
before the dream ends♪

903
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:53,960
♪We drift along in this dazzling world♪

904
00:43:54,180 --> 00:43:58,130
♪Stumbling through every change
life brings♪

905
00:43:58,130 --> 00:44:01,180
♪The true courage
is simply not looking back♪

906
00:44:01,760 --> 00:44:08,060
♪I finally understand:
The only constant is change♪

907
00:44:09,160 --> 00:44:14,590
♪Mother, I've grown up♪

908
00:44:15,940 --> 00:44:22,640
♪No longer try to fill every void♪

909
00:44:23,460 --> 00:44:30,300
♪No longer saddened by all the goodbyes♪

910
00:44:30,820 --> 00:44:37,790
♪No longer blame; no longer blame♪

911
00:44:38,560 --> 00:44:44,980
♪Mother, I've grown up♪

912
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:48,700
♪No longer try♪

913
00:44:48,720 --> 00:44:52,980
♪To fill every void♪

914
00:44:52,980 --> 00:44:56,590
♪No longer saddened♪

915
00:44:56,620 --> 00:45:00,220
♪By all the goodbyes♪

916
00:45:00,220 --> 00:45:03,860
♪No longer blame♪

917
00:45:04,120 --> 00:45:07,750
♪Love that led nowhere♪
